						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Vīrēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to 16th century on the palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>States that Chadaraṁgga Vīrayya constructed a <hi rend="italic">maṭham</hi> called Nirāsimaṭham and consecrated a <hi rend="italic">linga</hi> called Gōkarṇṇa, probably in the <hi rend="italic">maṭham.</hi> The prefix <hi rend="italic">chada raṁgga</hi> to the personal name Vīrayya indicates the proffession of chess game by the donor.</p>						

						</summary>
